# Project Requirements

This file documents all the hardware, software, and dependencies needed to run the CS2 Arduino Bomb Timer project.

## Software Requirements

### For Arduino Development

- **Arduino IDE** v1.8.0 or later ([Download](https://www.arduino.cc/en/software))
- **Arduino Board Support Package** for your microcontroller
  - Arduino AVR Boards (built-in with IDE)
  - Or custom package for your board type

### For Server Development

- **Node.js** v14.0.0 or later ([Download](https://nodejs.org/))
- **npm** v6.0.0 or later (comes with Node.js)
- **Git** (optional, for version control)

### Counter-Strike 2

- **Steam** installed and running
- **Counter-Strike 2** installed (free-to-play)
- **Administrator access** to modify CS2 config files

## Hardware Requirements

### Microcontroller

- **Arduino Uno** (recommended for beginners)
- **Arduino Mega** (optional, if you need more pins)
- **Arduino Nano** (optional, for compact builds)
- Other Arduino-compatible boards with at least 6 digital pins and 1 analog input

### Display & Indicators

- **16x2 LCD Display** (HD44780 compatible)
  - Parallel interface (4-bit or 8-bit mode)
  - Operating voltage: 5V
- **LED** (any color)
  - Standard 5mm LED (3-20mA)
- **Resistor**
  - 220Ω or 330Ω (for LED current limiting)

### Connectivity

- **USB Cable** (Type A to Type B or Mini-B)
  - Connects Arduino to PC for programming and power
  - Supports serial communication at 9600 baud

### Breadboard & Wiring (Optional but Recommended)

- **Breadboard** (400-point or larger)
- **Jumper wires** (various lengths)
- **Potentiometer** 10kΩ (optional, for LCD contrast adjustment)

## Network Requirements

### Local Network

- **Windows PC / Mac / Linux** with CS2 installed
- **Arduino connected via USB** to the same PC
- **Localhost network access** (127.0.0.1:3000)
- **No internet required** (all communication is local)

## Installation Instructions

### 1. Install Node.js Dependencies

Navigate to the server folder and install required packages:

```bash
cd server
npm install
```

This installs:

- `express` - Web server framework
- `body-parser` - JSON request parsing
- `serialport` - Arduino serial communication

### 2. Configure Arduino

1. Install Arduino IDE from https://www.arduino.cc/en/software
2. Connect your Arduino via USB cable
3. In Arduino IDE:
   - Tools → Board → Select your board type
   - Tools → Port → Select the COM port (e.g., COM3)
4. Upload [arduino/lcd_timer/lcd_timer.ino](../arduino/lcd_timer/)

### 3. Setup Counter-Strike 2

1. Copy [cs2-gsi/gamestate_integration_arduino.cfg](../cs2-gsi/)
2. Paste into your CS2 config folder (see [cs2-gsi/README.md](../cs2-gsi/) for path)
3. Restart Counter-Strike 2

### 4. Run the Server

```bash
cd server
node index.js
```

Expected output:

```
Serial connected: COM3
GSI server listening on http://localhost:3000
```

## Operating System Support

| OS                | Status             | Notes                               |
| ----------------- | ------------------ | ----------------------------------- |
| **Windows 10/11** | ✅ Fully Supported | Recommended; uses COM ports         |
| **Linux**         | ✅ Fully Supported | Use `/dev/ttyUSB*` for serial       |
| **macOS**         | ✅ Fully Supported | Use `/dev/tty.usbmodem*` for serial |

## Bandwidth & Performance

- **Serial Communication**: 9600 baud (~1.2 KB/s)
- **HTTP Requests**: ~500 bytes per request
- **Update Frequency**: ~30 Hz (30 requests/second from CS2)
- **Network Load**: Minimal (localhost only)
- **CPU Usage**: <1% (all cores)

## Recommended Specifications

### PC/Laptop

- **OS**: Windows 10+, macOS 10.15+, or Ubuntu 18.04+
- **RAM**: 2GB minimum (4GB+ recommended)
- **Storage**: 500MB free space
- **USB Ports**: At least 1 available

### Arduino Setup

- **Power**: 5V USB power (500mA)
- **Temperature**: 0-50°C operating range
- **Humidity**: Non-condensing environment

## Optional Enhancements

### Additional Components

- **7-segment display** - For alternative countdown display
- **Buzzer** - Audio feedback for bomb events
- **RGB LED** - Different colors for each bomb state
- **Relay module** - Control external devices (lights, horn, etc.)

### Software Upgrades

- Higher baud rate (115200) - Requires code changes on both ends
- WiFi module (ESP8266) - Replace USB with WiFi connectivity
- OLED display - Smaller, more modern alternative to LCD

## Troubleshooting

### Missing Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### Arduino Board Not Found

- Verify USB cable is properly connected
- Check Device Manager for "USB Serial Device"
- Try different USB ports on your PC
- Update Arduino IDE to latest version

### Serial Port Permission Issues (Linux/macOS)

```bash
sudo usermod -a -G dialout $USER
# Logout and login again
```

### CS2 GSI Not Working

- Verify config file exists in correct CS2 folder
- Check file permissions (should be readable)
- Restart Counter-Strike 2 completely
- Check Windows Firewall settings

## Versioning

| Component        | Version | Purpose               |
| ---------------- | ------- | --------------------- |
| Node.js          | v14+    | Server runtime        |
| Arduino IDE      | v1.8+   | Sketch compilation    |
| Counter-Strike 2 | Latest  | Game                  |
| Express          | ^5.2.1  | Web framework         |
| SerialPort       | ^13.0.0 | Arduino communication |

